  - m_Id: 46012689939509248
    m_Localized: Armed with his trusty whip and a jawline that could cut garlic, Antonio is the boldest (and most accident-prone) of the monster-slaying Belpaeses. Unlike his ancestors, who had years of rigorous training, his primary qualifications include looking good in a billowy shirt and swinging wildly until the problem goes away. If anything takes him down, it’ll be his own stupidity—not the undead.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480768
    m_Localized: Born from scandal, raised in spite, and dramatically brooding ever since, Arca clings to the idea that he’s of noble vampiric descent. His only proof? A filthy, barely legible note that smells suspiciously like pigsty. With a name that sounds important and firepower to match, he’s determined to burn his way to respect—one overcompensating fireball at a time.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480769
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Cavallo likes cherries!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480770
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Christine is into pagan things
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480771
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Clerici uses holy water! Its super effective!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480772
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Dommario likes THE book.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480773
    m_Localized: Monster slayer? Sure. Monster business partner? If the price is right. Gennaro Belpaese may share his family’s knack for killing the undead, but he prefers a more… entrepreneurial approach. Armed with twin blades and an even sharper tongue, he’s just as likely to strike a deal as he is to strike a killing blow—whichever pays better.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480774
    m_Localized: Magic is dangerous, they said. It’s untrustworthy, they warned. Imelda heard all that—and promptly ignored it. While her family swings whips like it’s the Middle Ages, she prefers raining arcane destruction from a safe distance. Sure, she’s the black sheep, but when the undead come knocking, guess who suddenly loves a well-placed fireball?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480775
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Krochi looks like a devil
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480776
    m_Localized: Raised by Porta, feared by everyone else, Lama Ladonna doesn’t just win battles—she ends them. A warrior of legendary skill and terrifying presence, her mere arrival on the battlefield has been known to make enemies lose their nerve… and their dignity. Those lucky enough to lack bowels might stand a chance. The rest? Well, they’d better hope she’s in a good mood.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480777
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Mortaccio uses his own bones as weapons
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480778
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Pasqualina has a {db.Cards.Card_A_1_Runetracer.Name}
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array:
        - rid: 2833696724673101824
  - m_Id: 46012689960480779
    m_Localized: Poe has few friends not because he’s lacking in charm — though he is — but because his all-garlic diet makes him unbearable to be around. This has made him an unlikely, but highly efficient monster-hunter, with the ability to clear rooms faster than a warewolf at full moon. His pitiful, lonely life has led him to reflect on an inner strength others overlook. His defenses may seem weak, but they’re his greatest power, drawn from solitude to face any threat.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480780
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Poppea Bio
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480781
    m_Localized: From pigsty to power, Porta Ladonna never lets opportunity—or a foolish noble—go to waste. Clever, charming, and utterly ruthless, she used one romantic tryst to secure wealth, then promptly ditched the count to carve out her own empire. Some say she’s a gold-digger, but Porta prefers the term self-made woman—and she’s not carrying anyone who can’t keep up.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480782
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Pugnala has a thingamagig
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 46012689960480783
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Zi-Assunta has a sacred cup of coffee
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 91365965080551424
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>The ghost of an old lady who used to steal supermarket carts.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
        Array: []
  - m_Id: 91365965118300160
    m_Localized: PLACEHOLDER<br>Giovanna Bio
    m_Metadata:
